Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.12,0:00:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Blood pressure, 120 over 80.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.33,0:00:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Pulse, 92.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.50,0:00:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I will now remove the bullet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.51,0:00:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I have removed the bullet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.60,0:00:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The removal is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.35,0:00:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little early to be relieved;
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.90,0:00:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we must still reinforce the walls\Nof the damaged blood vessel.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.82,0:00:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Uh-huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.90,0:00:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Get the proline ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.15,0:00:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.42,0:02:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Blood pressure, 128 over 72.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.13,0:02:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Pulse, 88.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.51,0:02:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems the anesthesia is still working.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.77,0:02:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.77,0:02:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best to survive...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.70,0:02:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Boyer...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.41,0:02:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like yours went well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.12,0:03:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.20,0:03:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The surgery did...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.62,0:03:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The mayor died.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.13,0:03:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I-Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.17,0:03:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a shame...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.55,0:03:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You act as though\Nit's none of your concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.18,0:03:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the very one who abandoned\Nour team just before surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.97,0:03:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... but,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.39,0:03:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that child was brought in\Nbefore the mayor...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.23,0:03:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it matter, who was first?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.69,0:03:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is, because you selfishly\Npulled out of our team,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.82,0:03:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we were forced to try to fill\Nthe vacuum you created!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.32,0:03:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But... Listen to me! I...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.28,0:03:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You upset the teamwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.53,0:03:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,By order of the Director,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.33,0:03:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I instructed you to perform the surgery on the mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.87,0:03:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But you... You ignored me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.04,0:03:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,B-but, Chief, at that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.25,0:03:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The success of a surgery depends upon trust among the entire staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.42,0:03:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But you made a grand stand play!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.84,0:04:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I have already reported this\Nto the Director.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.18,0:04:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He greatly regrets this incident, which has lowered the prestige of this hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.40,0:04:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.86,0:04:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.20,0:04:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait a minute!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.20,0:04:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.49,0:04:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,At present, that child's blood pressure\Nis 114 over 82; pulse, 84.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.50,0:04:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,His vitals are very stable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.92,0:04:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...\NThat's good...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.26,0:04:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... That operation...\NIt was wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.94,0:05:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to get some sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.26,0:06:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.64,0:06:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what will happen to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.31,0:06:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just like him...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.52,0:06:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Reinhardt in ICU\Nis complaining that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.90,0:06:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,she just can't sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.28,0:06:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't we give her something\Nto help her sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.03,0:06:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma, are you listening to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.49,0:06:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.20,0:06:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case,\Ngive her one Halcyon tablet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.21,0:06:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That man! He's been unfocused\Nall day long.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.89,0:06:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.72,0:06:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Becker!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.22,0:06:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems you've had a trying time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.02,0:06:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Has the Director\Nhanded down his judgment?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.81,0:06:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I warned you, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.02,0:07:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you the hospital\Nis ruled by politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.86,0:07:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If you played your cards right,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.95,0:07:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,your future would have been\Nsmooth sailing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.99,0:07:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... I guess this means you and I\Nare in the same boat now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.92,0:07:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, don't be so depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.25,0:07:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll get a chance\Nto redeem your reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.42,0:07:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go have some drinks.\NIt'll cheer you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.18,0:07:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.60,0:07:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I still need to get a statement\Nfrom the girl twin...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.90,0:07:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't discuss that with you now,\NDetective!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.11,0:07:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That girl is gone from her room!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.65,0:07:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.70,0:07:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That girl is always\Nslipping out of her room
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.03,0:07:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and wandering through the hospital!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.63,0:08:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.67,0:08:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.52,0:08:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.15,0:08:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And so...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.60,0:08:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Eisler Memorial Hospital has\Nproven to be
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.23,0:08:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the nation's leading medical facility.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.24,0:08:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That is first and foremost,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.53,0:08:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the result of our being blessed with such excellent personnel such as you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.08,0:08:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I am sincerely grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.46,0:08:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.50,0:08:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,unfortunately, the Mayor died\Nhere in this hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.17,0:08:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But, as always,\Nwe had done our utmost to save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.96,0:08:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The public's evaluation of this hospital\Nhas not changed one bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.05,0:08:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's have a round of applause\Nfor Dr. Boyer and Dr. Eisen,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.14,0:08:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,who strived to the end\Nto save the Mayor's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.49,0:09:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked at your paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.08,0:09:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you will continue to\Nwork on your research.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.01,0:09:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Director Heinemann!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.80,0:09:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... I must apologize\Nfor my actions...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.35,0:09:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.64,0:09:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What's done is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.52,0:09:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Director?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.90,0:09:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You did what you thought you should.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.94,0:09:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's leave it at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.86,0:09:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Director...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.49,0:09:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And now let's have a word from\Nthe Head of Neurosurgery!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.78,0:09:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Pardon me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.29,0:09:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm being called up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.50,0:10:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.54,0:10:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.33,0:10:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the newly appointed...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.00,0:10:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Boyer, please...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.05,0:10:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Please come this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.51,0:10:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, what is the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.34,0:10:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If you wish to remain at this hospital,\Nyou may do so,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.76,0:10:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but you'd better give up the idea of\Nrising any further as a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.77,0:10:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be impossible for someone with a flawed character such as yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.77,0:10:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll recognize your skill as a surgeon,\Nbut that is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.44,0:10:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You should also give up any ideas of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.03,0:10:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,presenting any papers\Nat future conferences.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.32,0:10:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But, sir... Please listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.32,0:10:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you wish to move\Nto another hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.41,0:10:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no intention of\Nwriting you a recommendation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.29,0:10:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This means it's no use for you\Nto have any ambition.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.08,0:10:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You may consider your path to becoming the doctor you envisioned closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.93,0:11:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Surgery requires teamwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.89,0:11:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Only with the help of each\Nand every one of you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.94,0:11:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,can a life be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.16,0:11:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.37,0:11:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva, won't you talk to your father\Nfor me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.29,0:11:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't done anything wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.38,0:11:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I just operated on\Nan emergency case
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.84,0:11:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in the order in which\Nhe was brought in!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.48,0:11:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's... your engagement ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.31,0:11:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You're such a fool...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.40,0:11:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.53,0:12:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.99,0:12:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, Dr. Norden,\Ndon't you look elegant?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.62,0:12:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,As do you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.04,0:12:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You're more beautiful\Nthan ever tonight, Eva.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.16,0:12:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What a laugh, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.99,0:12:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,After coming across\NDirector Heinemann's paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.87,0:12:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I came here to Germany,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.33,0:12:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and he made me what I am today...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.63,0:12:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that I think about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.96,0:12:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose that paper\Nthat I was so impressed by
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.71,0:12:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,was probably written for him\Nby someone somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.22,0:13:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that he was using me...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.35,0:13:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but I believed,\Nwhen I reached a certain position,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.89,0:13:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I would be able to work on research\Nof my choice to my heart's content.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.03,0:13:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.32,0:13:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Saving people's lives is what's most important to a doctor!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.41,0:13:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You're wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.45,0:13:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no distinction\Nbetween people's lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.83,0:13:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.96,0:13:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You say there's a flaw\Nin my character?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.17,0:13:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.46,0:13:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You call yourself a doctor;\Nbut you're just money hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.01,0:13:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That bastard... That bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.18,0:13:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He's better off dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.73,0:13:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I have you to thank...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.40,0:13:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You opened my eyes, as a doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.78,0:13:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You must do your best to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.69,0:14:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I threw everything away\Nin order to operate on you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.24,0:14:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how far I went\Nin order to bring you back to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.15,0:14:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You know your name, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.15,0:14:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Your name is Anna Liebert,\Nisn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.24,0:14:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, didn't I, Detective?\NIt's too soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.87,0:14:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't anything be done, Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.08,0:14:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, she saw her parents\Nshot to death before her very eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.09,0:15:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,She has no physical wounds,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.13,0:15:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but extreme trauma seems to have\Nbrought on amnesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.05,0:15:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you please refrain from trying to get a statement from her for a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.14,0:15:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a difficult case, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.02,0:15:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The victim was\Nan East German diplomat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.19,0:15:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't solve this quickly,\Nthe BKA will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.48,0:15:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Those guys always come and steal
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.61,0:15:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the thunder from us state police!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.24,0:15:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't got the time to take it slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.20,0:15:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What if we do this?\NWe let her see her brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.74,0:15:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll be relieved to see him\Nand her memory might return.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.46,0:15:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot agree on such a gamble-\None suggested by an amateur, at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.38,0:15:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, Dr. Tenma\Nwill probably not permit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.59,0:15:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.76,0:15:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the doctor\Nin charge of her brother Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.30,0:15:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck\Nam I supposed to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.06,0:15:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.10,0:16:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem to be in a daze.\NYou look awfully tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.40,0:16:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been so busy\Nwith emergency surgeries.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.49,0:16:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They've been working you\Nto the bone...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.82,0:16:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,ever since you were\Ndemoted from Chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.32,0:16:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.08,0:16:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It actually makes me feel better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.83,0:16:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, now... Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.33,0:16:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, I've just been paged.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.84,0:16:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so tired,\Nbut you still have work to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.84,0:16:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The more diligent you are,\Nthe worse it'll be for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.18,0:16:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at this, Director Heinemann...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.31,0:16:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,See all the gifts\Nand letters of encouragement.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.56,0:16:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There are mountains of them\Nin his sister's room, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.15,0:16:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,After losing their parents\Nthese two only have each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.65,0:16:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The mass media keeps reporting on their heartbreaking plight, and this is the result.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.40,0:16:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as this hospital is concerned,\Nthey're nothing but an inconvenience;
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.24,0:16:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,what with no sign of anyone paying\Ntheir medical expenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.95,0:16:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.04,0:16:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So their story is a pitiful one-\Nthat's just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.75,0:16:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.41,0:17:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That means this hospital is\Ngarnering attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.96,0:17:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,For that reason alone,\Nthese kids are valuable...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.96,0:17:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.42,0:17:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.38,0:17:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.34,0:17:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll give the media\Na photo of the siblings together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.02,0:17:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the media keeps asking\Nfor something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.52,0:17:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.85,0:17:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be a picture\Nof the orphaned siblings
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.31,0:17:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,trying their best to live\Nwithin the warmhearted care
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.36,0:17:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of our hospital's staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.03,0:17:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But the boy's doctor says it is still too early to allow them to see each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.49,0:17:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's on his case?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.62,0:17:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.54,0:17:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Dismiss him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.04,0:17:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.29,0:17:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no need to give that man\Na position that gets so much attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.55,0:17:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Take Dr. Tenma off the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.47,0:17:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.26,0:17:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a heartwarming gift\Nfrom the citizens.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.76,0:17:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you have one?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.43,0:17:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.86,0:18:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you feel, Mrs. Hankel?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.28,0:18:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to you, I feel quite well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.03,0:18:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Your stitches will be removed soon,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.29,0:18:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so it won't be long\Nuntil you're released.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.87,0:18:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be able to go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.25,0:18:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but as I said, you must rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.63,0:18:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.96,0:18:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Give Mrs. Hankel regular doses
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.84,0:18:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of an anticonvulsant\Nand a hypotensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.93,0:18:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.39,0:18:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.10,0:18:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.69,0:18:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They let her see her brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.90,0:18:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Then she gave a loud scream and...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.57,0:18:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you bring them together?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.12,0:19:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.46,0:19:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Take her back to her room, quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.67,0:19:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.25,0:19:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Boyer, what is the meaning of this?\NWhy the camera?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.80,0:19:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... We're going to give the media a picture of the emotional
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.93,0:19:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,meeting of the two children.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.51,0:19:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Who allowed you to do such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.39,0:19:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the boy's doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.02,0:19:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You have been dismissed\Nas Johan's doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.31,0:19:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,As of today, he is my patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.61,0:19:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided that it would be fine\Nto let them see each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.11,0:19:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Those children...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.45,0:19:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't make those children fodder\Nfor the media!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.62,0:19:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it by order of the Director.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.12,0:19:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it would be best for you\Nnot to fight it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.20,0:19:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the one who saved this boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.08,0:19:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a duty to protect him\Nuntil he is completely healed!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.83,0:19:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's the case,\Ntake a look at the boy's reaction!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.05,0:19:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as he saw his sister,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.85,0:20:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,he extended his hand and cried tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.52,0:20:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He regained consciousness\Nand showed a normal reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.52,0:20:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That means the surgery\Nwas a great success.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.36,0:20:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job. Your work is done now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.23,0:20:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back to where you belong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.67,0:20:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it...\NDon't make me laugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.55,0:20:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Who cares what the Director says?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.67,0:20:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Who cares what the Chief says?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.14,0:20:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all money and power hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.43,0:20:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn them!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.57,0:20:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I... I am not wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.21,0:21:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home, Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.92,0:21:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Father? Are you in your room?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.19,0:21:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.65,0:21:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you still in a meeting at this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.46,0:21:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, are you asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.92,0:21:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.11,0:22:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That bastard... He's better off dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.94,0:04:50.40,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mayor Roddecker, who collapsed\Nwhile on holiday,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.40,0:04:52.98,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}has passed away at the hospital.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.07,0:04:56.49,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Upon hearing this unexpected news,\Npeople have been arriving{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.49,0:04:59.15,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}at the Mayor's office\Nwith bouquets of flowers,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.15,0:05:01.70,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}many reminiscing on\Nthe life of the Mayor.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.20,0:05:05.87,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A press conference has just been held\Nat Eisler Memorial Hospital{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.87,0:05:07.50,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}where the Mayor was taken.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.54,0:05:11.04,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The cause of\NMayor Roddecker's death{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.04,0:05:12.96,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}was due to a cerebral infarction\Nstemming from{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.96,0:05:15.21,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}a severe emphraxis\Nof the inner carotid artery.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.21,0:05:20.47,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We did everything we could for him,\Nbut it caused severe brain swelling,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.47,0:05:23.10,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}which resulted in\Nthis unfortunate outcome.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.69,0:05:36.65,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In the case of the murder of\NMr. and Mrs. Liebert late last night...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.19,0:05:39.74,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Judging from the signs of\Na search in the rooms,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.74,0:05:41.20,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}police believe\Nthis may have been a robbery...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.49,0:05:44.12,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}or perhaps the act of\Na political terrorist{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.12,0:05:46.66,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}against this couple\Nwho had fled here from their country.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.66,0:05:49.00,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A two-pronged investigation\Nis under way.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.33,0:05:52.42,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Of this couple's twin children, the son,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.42,0:05:54.79,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}who received a gunshot wound\Nto the head{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.29,0:05:56.80,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}underwent successful surgery, but...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.80,0:06:00.30,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}has still to regain consciousness.\NHe is listed in critical condition.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.05,0:06:03.34,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now, for the weather...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.52,0:13:17.74,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We are scholars, first and foremost.\NIsn't that right?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.91,0:13:25.41,Default - Italic,,0,0,0,,{\i1}After all, people's lives\Naren't created equal.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.93,0:05:27.85,Default - Italic an8,,0,0,0,,{\i1\an8}As for naming a successor,\Na city official explained that{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.85,0:05:30.56,Default - Italic an8,,0,0,0,,{\i1\an8}concrete steps will be taken as soon as possible.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.29,0:22:36.96,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}And slowly, you come to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.51,0:22:44.39,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It's all as it should be
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.26,0:22:53.81,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You can only do so much
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.98,0:22:59.40,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}If you're game enough
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.82,0:23:07.20,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You could place your trust in me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.21,0:23:16.29,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}For the love of life
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.42,0:23:21.63,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}There's a trade off
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.43,0:23:28.39,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}We could lose it all
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.39,0:23:33.31,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}But we'll go down fighting
